From Andrew Geweke Subject LC II Slowdowns I am currently managing among many other labs a lab with three LC IIs a Mac Plus with MB external HD and a LaserWriter II My problem The LC IIs seem to intermittently slow to a snail's These LC IIs have MB RAM VRAM and a Quantum HD I have reformatted the drive with Hard Disk Toolkit and it gives a very respectable overall rating to this drive so it's not the I have reinstalled System MS Word MS Works and so on all from the master In short I have done everything I can think of in I am not a hardware hacker though I pop cases fairly But nothing The problem is intermittent and The mouse always moves smoothly floppies always run at the same speed but occasionally for about hours at a time a machine will run like it was running on a MHz not a MHz It is VERY frustrating and makes it nearly It does seem to worsen with increasing disk Has anyone encountered this problem before Has anyone got any ideas They would be much Andrew Geweke Andrew Geweke The Firing Squad BBS public access Usenet mail and Saint Paul Minnesota